{"entry_type":"status","summary":"Agent-2: Email adapter fully implemented — template rendering, recipient resolution, pluggable transport, 22 unit tests","detail":"Replaced EmailAdapter stub with full implementation. Three key features: (1) Template rendering — TEMPLATES record maps NotificationType to HTML+text email bodies with XSS-safe escaping. (2) Recipient resolution — RecipientResolver function type, default resolves '@'-containing strings, custom resolvers for user ID lookup. (3) Pluggable EmailTransport interface — InMemoryTransport for dev/test, swap for real SMTP/SES/SendGrid. Added 22 tests covering send, recipient resolution, template rendering for all 4 types, HTML escaping, custom transport, and transport error handling. All 93 tests pass, TypeScript compiles clean. The adapter conforms to NotificationAdapter interface and is already wired into NotificationService via registerAdapter().","tags":["implementation","email","adapters"],"scope":"src/adapters/","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN10X2WN1NAN6ABMA8FT993Y","timestamp":"2026-03-31T04:02:22.742Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"User notification preferences with email toggle, frequency, and category subscriptions, checked by NotificationService before dispatch","detail":"Preferences model has: emailEnabled (global toggle), emailFrequency (immediate/daily_digest/weekly_digest), subscribedCategories (set of NotificationType). PreferencesService stores preferences in-memory keyed by userId, with sensible defaults (all enabled, immediate frequency). NotificationService gets a PreferencesService injected and checks preferences before calling sendNotification. This keeps the preference check in the service layer (not the adapter) since preferences are a business concern, not a transport concern.","tags":["architecture"],"scope":"src/models/user-preferences.ts","agent_id":"agent-3","id":"01KN10YVYNWT5K3MV9VANYVER5","timestamp":"2026-03-31T04:03:21.173Z"}
