{"entry_type":"status","summary":"Agent-10: Fixed notification delivery ordering — per-recipient promise chain, 2 new tests, all 222 tests pass","detail":"Root cause: sendNotification() is async (awaits adapter.send()), but concurrent events for the same recipient had no ordering guarantee — a slow first delivery could be overtaken by a fast second one. Fix: Added a recipientQueues map to NotificationService that chains promises per recipient. sendNotification() appends to the chain so deliveries for the same recipient are serialized, while different recipients still run concurrently. Core delivery logic extracted to private deliverNotification(). Added 2 tests: (1) concurrent events for same recipient are delivered in order despite artificial delay, (2) different recipients are NOT queued against each other. All 222 tests pass.","tags":[],"scope":"src/services/notification.service.ts","agent_id":"agent-10","id":"01KN128ER37E4X0EZNA8QZ4QS5","timestamp":"2026-03-31T04:26:03.907Z"}

